    "comment": "Rationale: GluD1 is shown to primarily localize to the postsynaptic density of excitatory synapses in CA1 neurons of the mouse hippocampus (Figure 8 g, h). Antibodies used for electron microscopy analyses were validated by western blotting using GRID1-/- and did not cross react with GluD2 in HEK cells (Figure 5a,b). Experimental description: western blot: HEK cells; no information on plasmid DNA used, they might be mouse cDNAs for GluD1 and GluD2 because they test antibodies and mRNA probes with them.\n\nElectron microscopy: mouse brain section",
